{
  "texts": [
    "In contrast, the complex computation in the GC implementation of Algorithm 3 runs on only 10 drones that clear the conditional on line GC4.",
    "This experiment clearly justifies our use of secret-sharing based MPC in Pd-Mpc over a garbled circuit-based implementation.For a given city-scale drone deployment (e.g., 𝑛=100 drones), observe that the per-query mobile data usage increases in proportion to the drone density in the citizen's vicinity.",
    "The reader may question why we observe this trend, given that the size of the garbled circuit is fixed by the value of 𝑛, and does not depend on drone density.",
    "The answer to this question lines in how Algorithm 3 is implemented atop EMP, as discussed below.Recall that EMP lacks default support for oblivious if statements, and relies on the programmer to suitably design the algorithm to ensure that any side channels due to the lack of this support are suppressed.",
    "In particular, EMP will not compile Algorithm 3 (as shown) because the predicate used in the conditional statement on line GC4 is input-dependent."
  ]
}